<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 2:24AM CDT  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Pike
and south central Montgomery Counties through 300 AM CDT...
At 224 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Petrey, or 10 miles north of Luverne, moving east at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Troy, Goshen, Kent, Ansley, Troy Municipal Airport, Antioch, Troy
University, Lapine, Orion and Mossy Grove.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
